[1] France (Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes)
Date: Fri 16 Jun 2017
Source: La Montagne [in French, trans. Corr.SB, edited]
http://www.lamontagne.fr/montmarault/faits-divers/allier/2017/06/16/une-cinquantaine-d-enfants-touches-par-une-potentielle-intoxication-alimentaire-a-montmarault-allier_12446912.html


57 children and adolescents attending different schools in Montmarault (Allier) showed the same symptoms on Thu [15 Jun 2017]: nausea, vomiting, diarrhea.

16 absences were recorded in nursery school, 26 in elementary school, and 15 in college. However, not all of them had lunch at the canteen. External students have also been affected.

Are the water or meals taken in common at the canteen by all the affected students responsible? Is this a virus? We still do not know. The necessary action has already been undertaken to have an answer as soon as possible.

Everything has been done pending the results of the samples.

Tests made by the Regional Health Agency and the departmental council were carried out on the various items served at lunch. Samples were also taken from the water. The results of these analyses could be known over next week.

Bottles of water were bought and distributed to the students. The consumption of tap water was suspended until further notice at the college.

On Friday [16 Jun 2017], there were still 23 absences in kindergarten and 40 in primary school, while the number of absent schoolchildren was stable.

